gn=left class=m><span class=title> Dumb Epic questions - sorry...</span><hr size=1> Okies I have been really lucky with my Epic so far but am petrified of screwing up at the end (am doing it for multiple Rogues). I know a lot of this stuff has been covered in other threads, I'm just double checking everything (pre-Epic paranioa). I really don't wanna mess up for me and my fellow thieves.<br>
<br>
So in no particular order, here goes ...<br>
<br>
a) To spawn The General I hand in the Box to the pulled mob, from behind with sneak (but not hide) the General pops and the pulled mob stays up?<br>
<br>
b) The pulled mob is any mob from the DE camp? If so why the attraction with the Coercer? Other than she's a hottie <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
c) The spawn time of the camp mobs is 8 RL hours? They are only there at night though?<br>
<br>
d) Just how rare is the Cazic Quill (1 in 3? 1 in 10?) and what is it, a blade?<br>
<br>
e) When Stanos asks you to return &quot;those blades Vilnius made you work so hard for&quot;. He is referring to the Jagged Diamond Dagger and The Cazic Quill? The walkthrough is fairly exlpicit on the final hand-in, its probably just the quest text is misleading?<br>
<br>
f) Anything else I should know? Any other advice.<br>
<br>
g) Anyone on E'ci free on Sunday 12 noon EST wanna help? Heh <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulemacdushae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lemac Dushae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/24/01 10:55:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dumb Epic questions - sorry...</span><hr size=1> <br>
I'll help best I can.<br>
<br>
a)  You'd better hide incase he turns around mid-trade.  Generally the &quot;safe&quot; way is to open a trade window with 1cp.  If he rolls you, at least you don't loose your box.  If window stays open and you don't die, add box to window and click trade.<br>
<br>
b)  The hottie is the common pick because you pull with a monk and pumice.  Dispel her and she will come running.  Monk FD's (or real deaths occassionally..) and the inkies will walk home to the cabin.  She'll stop to rebuff herself.  While she's stopped, the rest keep going.  That means the General spawns away from the rest of them.<br>
<br>
c)  They no longer despawn at dawn, AFAIK they can spawn during the day as well.<br>
<br>
d)  Best guess has the quill at 1 in 10 chance.  It's a dagger.<br>
<br>
e)  That's my interpretation.<br>
<br>
f)   Patience, take your time, smooth and easy.  Just like the rest of our hiests.<br>
<br>
g)  Nope, Fennin Ro, but I wish ya luck anyway.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utemraeldarkfury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Temrael Darkfury</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/24/01 12:52:20 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dumb Epic questions - sorry...</span><hr size=1> Thanks for your help, just to clarify your first 3 answers...<br>
<br>
a) Do you mean you hand in the 1cp at the same the Box? I've never done that before, I expect that would have the desired effect followed by &quot;I'm not sure what to do with this&quot;.<br>
<br>
b) When I did the General last Sunday, for someone else, we just cleared the camp with the exception of one DE. If the spawn time is 8 hours, then with the camp clear obviously there is no-one to split her from? This being the case would you still pull her out of camp prior to the hand over? Would this ensure that when the General pops, The Coercer is on her way back and therefore doesn't add with the General pull?<br>
<br>
c) So this can be done anytime they are up? Hmm... do I want Bixxie or big-ass Undead adds? Heh<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utillaintheslacker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tillain the Slacker</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="   http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/24/01 1:20:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dumb Epic questions - sorry...</span><hr size=1>  a) The reason you hand in 1cp is to open a trade window becaus eif he turns while you have trade window open and with box in trade window ...well you are gonna get smacked. If she doesn't turn after you give the 1 copper then proceed to give the box. If you have successfully spawned general and you get owned then you can  *hopefully* rehide or you can die and get rezzed again. It matters not, as the general will stay up for about 20min after respawn (or so).<br>
<br>
b) by that time you don't need to pull her out if you have camp cleared (to my knowledge).<br>
<br>
c) Yes it would be beneficial to do it during daylight hours as the adds are pretty minor. Saves mana as well but honestly does't matter (IMO)<br>
<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udraziceci.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drazic Eci</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/24/01 3:25:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dumb Epic questions - sorry...</span><hr size=1> Ok, dumb question from one of the other Rogues from this upcoming raid, regarding on of the answers given here...<br>
<br>
&quot;a) The reason you hand in 1cp is to open a trade window because if he turns while you have trade window open and with box in trade window ...well you are gonna get smacked. If she doesn't turn after you give the 1 copper then proceed to give the box.&quot;<br>
<br>
Maybe im mis-reading somewhere or dont understand how no drop items work, but why bother testing the trade with 1cp. If she turns during book trade window and agros, cant you just hit cancel on the trade screen and book will return to inventory?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulemacdushae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lemac Dushae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/24/01 3:50:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dumb Epic questions - sorry...</span><hr size=1> <br>
Laggy connections (common when 50 some people flood a small zone and start casting spells) don't always help.  Using the worthless 1cp or it could be anything else, to open the window is a check to see if you get aggroed.  If the coast is clear (both from who you are trading with and other mobs in the area) add the box to the window, hit trade, and hope.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulindianae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lindianae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/24/01 9:53:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dumb Epic questions - sorry...</span><hr size=1> When we did it we cleared the cabin of all but one. Monk then pulled that one away for hand in. This means that the General is alone in the cabin and an easy pull. This is even more important to do if you are doing multiple Generals.<br>
<br>
Alvarny <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utemraeldarkfury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Temrael Darkfury</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/ring20.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/31/01 5:38:24 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dumb Epic questions - sorry...</span><hr size=1> Well just to update you all, Sundays raid was not a complete success.  <br>
<br>
Kedge Robe dropped off Coercer, which was nice, and we got an RBG but two out of our four quest Rogues (me being one) were aggroed on hand in. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
The pull team weren't really up for pulling the last DE out of the Hut and I think that may have been half the problem. I did the hand-in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  inside</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the cabin. I was hid/snuck behind the DE and double-clicked 1cp on him. The first click knocked off hide and the second brought up a trade window. I added the box to the trade window and as I clicked &quot;Give&quot;.... a zombie slapped me. I thought the hut was cleared but perhaps one popped behind me.<br>
<br>
Anyway, the DE aggroed and I was CoH'ed back to the raid, seconds ticked by and no General, I thought I was going to puke. Slowly it sunk in that he was not going to make an appearance for me. I petitioned but the GMs said as they couldn't verify wether I was agro'ed before I turned it in there was nothing they could do.<br>
<br>
Anyway, enough of the sob stories, we are giving it another go on Eci this Sunday Noon EST and you are welcome to come and join us if you can.<br>
<br>
A couple more questions though...<br>
<br>
1) Does the DE need to be pulled from the hut? I think this would help as there are a lot of undead pops in the hut even during the day.<br>
<br>
2) If a DE is pulled out by an FD puller, how much time do you have to do the hand-in before the DE turns to go back to the camp? I know the Coercer stops to buff but what about the melee ones?<br>
<br>
3) Anything else I haven't thought about? Seems rotten luck to lose half our General's<br>
<br>
I'm actually thinking about doing the quest again before Sunday as far as the Translated Note. That way if we screw up again Sunday I can pop next-door to Stanos and get another Box while I still have 30 people or whatever to do the General. To be honest I think I am just addicted to the rush that only comes from solo Hate raiding. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Temrael Darkfury<br>
51st Dark Elf Rogue<br>
&quot;Ideal for quick, descreet interventions&quot;<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utemraeldarkfury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Temrael Darkfury</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/ring20.gif" BORDER=0> at: 11/1/01 1:01:44 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uderkan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Derkan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/1/01 10:02:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dumb Epic questions - sorry...</span><hr size=1> Bah, screw the "open it with a CP".  I'll tell you why...<br>
First General raid of mine, hide/sneak , opened trade window<br>
with a copper, waited 3 seconds....no aggro, "Cool" i thought.<br>
Handed over box, as I was hitting trade a skelly spawned behind me.....I mean right as I was hitting trade.  Rogue<br>
dead, box gone, game over.<br>
<br>
<br>
My raid (2nd shot) cleared cabin save for the coercer.<br>
I like to clear it because other rogues can get<br>
a shot at the ishva robe, or with luck, the kedge.<br>
Hide/sneak , just handed over the box, waited maybe 1 second and hit trade.  Gen V spawned, and that mofo<br>
dropped my quill.  <br>
<br>
Quill rarity, dunno, I have done 5 or so Gen v raids,<br>
and perhaps 15 generals under my belt.  Mine is the<br>
only time I saw the quill drop.<br>
<br>
Yes, you can have a general v farm.  Just have rogues<br>
lined up and you can kill 20 of them if you like....<br>
<br>
But, screw the "open trade with a copper", especially at night.<br>
<br>
To clear the house, take a drood with you and harmony the<br>
other de's.  Easily keel'n<br>
<br>
<br>
Bleh<br>
~Derkan<br>
55 Rogue <br>
Lanys <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=2966.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3188.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3136.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3136.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3136.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3136.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers">The Back Alley<option value="thesafehousefrm13">Quests of Norrath<option value="thesafehousetherootcellar">The Root Cellar<option value="thesafehouselaboratory">Laboratory<option value="thesafehousefrm15">The Arena<option value="thesafehousefrm17">Anarchy's Grip